-- Cyprus Optimistic on Russian Loan, Cypriot Foreign Minister Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-09-12T06:22:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-12/cyprus-optimistic-on-russian-loan-cypriot-foreign-minister-says.html
Cyprus is optimistic that it will
reach an agreement with  Russia  for a 5 billion-euro ($6.4
billion) loan, Cypriot Foreign Minister Erato Kozakou-Markoulli
said in a live interview on Greek state-run channel  NET TV .  Discussions between the two countries are continuing and
are focused on the interest-rate level for the loan, Kozakou-
Markoulli said in the interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
